isDirected

public boolean isDirected()
Description copied from interface: Edge
Returns true if the edge is directed or false if it's undirected. Default is directed. Note that value is immutable.

Special cases:

  • If the edge has been created from an undirected graph, returns false.
  • If the edge has been created from a directed graph, returns true.
  • If the edge has been created from a mixed graph, returns the value set to the addEdge() method.

Specified by:
isDirected in interface Edge
Returns:
true if the edge is directed, false otherwise
